2117356.plan:
### Fitness Assessment & Goal Viability

You have an extensive endurance history across running, cycling, and swimming, with over 1800 runs and 800 rides logged. This provides a substantial aerobic foundation.

Your recent training shows a mix of all three disciplines, culminating in a very demanding weekend with a parkrun, a long swim, and a standard distance triathlon. Your statement of feeling "a little tired" is an understatement; this is significant load and warrants a dedicated recovery period.

Your 5k time of 22:32 at the Mile End parkrun gives a current VDOT of **43**. A sub-40 minute 10k requires a VDOT of **50**. Closing a 7-point VDOT gap by early November is highly ambitious. It is not impossible given your training history, but it will require consistent, high-quality work and a near-perfect run-up to your goal race.

This plan is structured to first recover from your recent events, then systematically build your running fitness towards this aggressive target. The initial week is deliberately light to ensure full recovery.

### Training Pace & Zone Recommendations

Your heart rate zones are largely correct. The primary zones for this plan (Zone 2, Zone 4, Zone 5) are aligned between your Strava settings and the Friel calculation method. No update is necessary.

| Zone | Strava HR Zones | Friel HR Zones (LTHR 160) | Recommendation |
| :--- | :--------------- | :------------------------- | :--------------- |
| 1    | 0-136 bpm        | 0-136 bpm                  | Match            |
| 2    | 136-142 bpm      | 136-142 bpm                | Match            |
| 3    | 142-152 bpm      | 144-150 bpm                | Mismatch         |
| 4    | 152-160 bpm      | 152-160 bpm                | Match            |
| 5    | 160+ bpm         | 160+ bpm                   | Match            |

The discrepancy in Zone 3 is irrelevant as we will not be targeting it.

Your VDOT is currently calculated from a parkrun where you noted you were not at maximum effort. To establish accurate training paces, you will perform a 5km time trial in Week 3. This will provide a true baseline to structure the key sessions for the remainder of the plan. Until then, quality sessions will be based on HR (Zone 4).

### Run a sub 40 minute 10k at the beginning of November Training Plan:

This is a 6-week plan. Schedule the sessions to fit your life, ensuring at least one rest day between [KEY] sessions. Your Tuesday club run can serve as an easy or recovery session. As an "Improviser", focus on completing the [KEY] and [IMPORTANT] sessions as a priority; the [STRETCH] sessions are optional extras if you have the time and energy.

---

**Week 1 (Off Week: 5 hours available)**
*Focus: Active Recovery. You are recovering from a significant race weekend. Do not push the intensity.*

*   **[IMPORTANT] Easy Run:** 45 minutes, strictly Zone 2.
*   **[IMPORTANT] S&C Session:** 30 minutes. Prioritise Routine A.
*   **[STRETCH] Social Run:** Your 60-minute Tuesday club run. Keep it social, heart rate in Zone 1/2.
*   **[STRETCH] Recovery Cross-Train:** 45-60 minutes easy cycling or swimming, Zone 1.
*   **[STRETCH] S&C Session:** 30 minutes. Routine B.

---

**Week 2 (On Week: 8 hours available)**
*Focus: Introduce intensity. Build aerobic volume.*

*   **[KEY] Threshold Run:** 15 min warm-up (Z1/2), then 2 x 10 minutes @ Zone 4, with 5 min Zone 1 recovery between reps. 10 min cool-down (Z1).
*   **[IMPORTANT] Long Run:** 75 minutes, steady Zone 2.
*   **[IMPORTANT] S&C Session:** 30 minutes. Prioritise Routine C.
*   **[IMPORTANT] Aerobic Cross-Train:** 90 minutes easy cycling or swimming, Zone 2.
*   **[STRETCH] Social Run:** Your 60-minute Tuesday club run. Zone 1/2.
*   **[STRETCH] S&C Session:** 30 minutes. Routine D.

---

**Week 3 (Off Week: 5 hours available)**
*Focus: Establish a VDOT baseline.*

*   **[KEY] 5km Time Trial:** 15 min warm-up with drills and 3-4 short strides. Run 5km at your best sustainable effort. 15 min cool-down. **You must use this result to calculate your new VDOT and associated training paces for the following weeks.**
*   **[IMPORTANT] Easy Run:** 60 minutes, Zone 2. This should be done 2-3 days after the time trial.
*   **[IMPORTANT] S&C Session:** 30 minutes. Prioritise Routine A.
*   **[STRETCH] Social Run:** Your 60-minute Tuesday club run. Use as a recovery run post-TT. Zone 1.

---

**Week 4 (On Week: 8 hours available)**
*Focus: Build volume and intensity with two quality sessions. Use your new VDOT paces from the Week 3 TT.*

*   **[KEY] Interval Run:** 15 min warm-up. 6 x 800m @ your new VDOT 'I' pace, with a 400m easy jog recovery after each. 15 min cool-down.
*   **[KEY] Threshold Run:** 15 min warm-up. 3 x 10 minutes @ your new VDOT 'T' pace (or Z4 HR), with 3 min jog recovery between reps. 15 min cool-down.
*   **[IMPORTANT] Long Run:** 90 minutes, steady Zone 2.
*   **[IMPORTANT] S&C Session:** 30 minutes. Prioritise Routine C.
*   **[STRETCH] Social Run:** Your 60-minute Tuesday club run. Zone 1/2.
*   **[STRETCH] Aerobic Cross-Train:** 60 minutes easy cycling or swimming, Zone 2.

*Flexibility Option: If well-recovered, you could stack the two [KEY] sessions on the same day (AM/PM) for a significant training stimulus, in the style of the Norwegian Method. For example, the Threshold Run in the morning and a reduced Interval Run (e.g., 4x800m) in the evening.*

---

**Week 5 (Off Week: 5 hours available)**
*Focus: Consolidate fitness on reduced volume.*

*   **[KEY] Threshold Run:** 15 min warm-up. 1 x 20-minute continuous block @ your VDOT 'T' pace. 15 min cool-down.
*   **[IMPORTANT] Easy Run:** 60 minutes, Zone 2.
*   **[IMPORTANT] S&C Session:** 30 minutes. Prioritise Routine A.
*   **[STRETCH] Social Run:** Your 60-minute Tuesday club run. Zone 1/2.
*   **[STRETCH] S&C Session:** 30 minutes. Routine B.

---

**Week 6 (On Week: Taper for Race)**
*Focus: Sharpen for race day. Reduce volume significantly, maintain some intensity.*

*   **[KEY] Race Pace Run:** To be done early in the week. 15 min warm-up. 4 x 1km at your goal 10k pace (4:00/km), with 400m jog recovery. 15 min cool-down. This session tests goal viability.
*   **[IMPORTANT] Easy Run:** 40 minutes, Zone 2.
*   **[STRETCH] Social Run:** Your Tuesday club run. Reduce to 45 minutes and keep it strictly Z1 recovery.
*   **[STRETCH] Pre-Race Shakeout:** The day before your race. 20 minutes easy running (Z1) with 3 x 100m strides at race pace.
*   **[STRETCH] S&C Session:** One light session (Routine D) early in the week. 20 mins max. No heavy lifting.
*   **RACE DAY:** Execute your sub-40 minute 10k attempt.

---

### S&C Plan

Perform the [IMPORTANT] session on an easy run day or rest day. The [STRETCH] session can be added on another easy day if you feel fresh. Focus on form over weight.

**Routine A: Stability & Core**
*   **Bodyweight Squats:** 3 sets of 15 reps. (Gym: Leg Press Machine)
*   **Plank:** 3 sets, 45-60 second hold. (Gym: No alternative needed)
*   **Glute Bridge:** 3 sets of 15 reps. (Gym: Hip Thrust Machine)
*   **Bird-Dog:** 3 sets of 10 reps per side (slow and controlled). (Gym: Cable Pallof Press)

**Routine B: Unilateral Strength**
*   **Walking Lunges:** 3 sets of 10 reps per leg. (Gym: Smith Machine Lunges)
*   **Single-Leg Romanian Deadlift (Bodyweight):** 3 sets of 12 reps per leg. (Gym: Leg Curl Machine)
*   **Push-ups:** 3 sets to near failure (modify on knees if needed). (Gym: Chest Press Machine)
*   **Side Plank:** 3 sets, 30-45 second hold per side. (Gym: No alternative needed)

**Routine C: Power & Dynamics**
*   **Jump Squats:** 3 sets of 10 reps. Focus on explosive movement. (Gym: Light Goblet Squats)
*   **Calf Raises:** 3 sets of 20 reps (use a step to increase range of motion). (Gym: Seated or Standing Calf Raise Machine)
*   **Russian Twists (Bodyweight):** 3 sets of 15 reps per side. (Gym: Torso Rotation Machine)
*   **Mountain Climbers:** 3 sets of 30 seconds. (Gym: No alternative needed)

**Routine D: Full Body Integration**
*   **Reverse Lunges:** 3 sets of 12 reps per leg. (Gym: Leg Press, single leg focus)
*   **Superman:** 3 sets of 15 reps. (Gym: Back Extension Machine)
*   **Dead Bug:** 3 sets of 10 reps per side. (Gym: Ab Crunch Machine, focusing on slow control)
*   **Bear Crawl:** 3 sets, crawl 10 metres forward and 10 metres back. (Gym: No alternative needed)

analyzed_activities.name: Maldon triathlon - Standard distance - Run
analyzed_activities.private_note: A fun local race that I've wanted to do for ages and I had a chance to do on a free weekend so I thought why not!  My swim wasn't great, so tried to hold steady power on the bike and was quite happy with that performance, on the run I tried to maintain as long as possible in zone 4, it's not representative for a VDOT score as I was definitely fatigued and I didn't go all out, but I was running strong the whole way, kept good form and pace was pretty good
